花字：Large Sky Area Multi-Object Fiber Spectroscopic Telescope (LAMOST)


------

Using China's largest optical telescope, astronomers have discovered a record number of unevolved stars rich in lithium, a key chemical element linking cosmology to the structure and evolution of stars. According to the study, the lithium contents of the nine stars are about three times higher than the lithium content of the sun.

